ffines pro non execucione officiorumEt de iiij li. xviij s. viij d. receptis per ipsum nunc cumputantem de magistro Blacker pro non execucione officij Magistri Revellorum tempore natalis domini vltimo preterito
Summa xxvj s. viij d.

Fines for non-performance of dutiesAnd (the accountant renders account) of 26s 8d received by the present accountant himself from Mr Blacker, for the non-performance of the office of master of the revels at Christmas-tide last past.
Total: 26s 8d

Stipendia musicorumEt de xxvj s. viij d. Solutis Willelmo Perryn musico pro anuali stipendio ei concesso per warrantum gubernatorum hospitij predicti gerens datum iiijto die ffebruarij anno regni dicte domine Regine xxijo
Summa xxvj s. viij d.

Musicians' stipends And (the accountant seeks to be allowed the sum) of 26s 8d paid to William Perryn, musician, for the annual stipend granted him by a warrant of the governors of the aforesaid Inn, dated on 4 February in twenty-second year of the reign of the said lady, Queen (Elizabeth).
Total: 26s 8d
...Et de iij li. vj s. viij d. Solutis magistro fferand vni capellanorum domine Regine pro commedia ostensa per warrantum gubernatorum gerens datum nono de die ffebruarij 1579...
...And (the accountant seeks to be allowed the sum) of £3 6s 8d paid to Mr Farrant, one of the lady queen's chaplains, for the comedy shown by a warrant of the governors, dated 9 February 1579...

div.note: Richard Farrant ('magistro fferand) was the deputy master of the children of the Chapel, 1576-80. The 'commedia' is not otherwise known; for the company's repertory, see Chambers, Elizabethan Stage, vol 2, pp 35-6.
